                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12439972" author="scotsmatrix" created="Wed, 4 Oct 2006 22:26:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;1) Can you provide any more info on what you think should be mentioned about Derby client?&lt;br/&gt;
2) Instead of JCC, what should the db2jcc.jar be?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12440027" author="kartha" created="Thu, 5 Oct 2006 05:47:34 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;1) readme.html&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;The Derby Network Server is a server framework that comes with Derby. The Derby Network Server works with the DB2 JCC JDBC driver; please read the Derby documentation on the differences between this driver and the embedded driver.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this can be modified to include Derby Client, something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;The Derby Network Server is a server framework that comes with Derby. The Derby Network Server works with the Derby Client driver as well as the DB2 JCC JDBC driver; please read the Derby documentation on the differences between the client and the embedded drivers.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2)example.html - no change needed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This one seems like a sysinfo message issue. It mentions &apos;Derby Client libraries (db2jcc.jar)&apos;  instead of the &apos;DB2 JCC Driver (db2jcc.jar) &apos; - which could be confusing. Anyways, this output is coming from the sysinfo, so not a doc issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12450089" author="scotsmatrix" created="Wed, 15 Nov 2006 16:19:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have the demo files checked out and see a readme.html file at the root, but I don&apos;t see &quot;frameworks&quot; in the directory structure.&lt;br/&gt;
Perhaps I don&apos;t have the correct info checked out?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I look a the content in the Readme file, I don&apos;t see the text you mention above &lt;br/&gt;
&quot;The Derby Network Server is a server framework that comes with Derby. The Derby Network Server works with the DB2 JCC JDBC driver; please read the Derby documentation on the differences between this driver and the embedded driver.&quot; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12450093" author="scotsmatrix" created="Wed, 15 Nov 2006 16:21:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I used this to check out the demo files&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;svn co&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/db/derby/code/trunk/java/demo&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/db/derby/code/trunk/java/demo&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12450106" author="fuzzylogic" created="Wed, 15 Nov 2006 16:35:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;frameworks is at the top level of the code tree. You would need to check out the whole code tree to get it, or check out the  frameworks directory to a separate directory. If you intend to generate a patch that includes changes to the demo files and frameworks, it will probably be most expedient to go ahead and check out the whole code tree:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;svn co &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/db/derby/code/trunk/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/db/derby/code/trunk/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12484502" author="scotsmatrix" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2007 18:09:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Per comments from Rajesh, I only updated the readme file. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attaching a patch for this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12484503" author="scotsmatrix" created="Tue, 27 Mar 2007 18:13:00 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Is the sysinfo error message something that the Derby community can fix? &lt;br/&gt;
If so, we need a separate issue for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12491350" author="bryanpendleton" created="Tue, 24 Apr 2007 17:08:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Laura, I proof-read your readme.html patch and it looks OK to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any reason we can&apos;t commit this now and resolve this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12492355" author="scotsmatrix" created="Fri, 27 Apr 2007 19:09:33 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 533181.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
